 <text>
  <front>
   <head>A SONG.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">the bright way that his honour directs him,</l>
     <l n="2" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">Oh all  let me beg you protect him.</l>
     <l n="3" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">gone my Dear — and left me here mourning;</l>
     <l n="4" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">I'le fancy him returning.</l>
     <l n="5" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">Returning, I'le think the great  Victorious,</l>
     <l n="6" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">With joy to my Arms as faithful as Glorious.</l>
     <l n="7" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">Against his bright Eyes, I am sure there's no standing;</l>
     <l n="8" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">He looks like a God, and moves as Commanding.</l>
     <l n="9" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">With a Face so Angelick the Foe will be charmed</l>
     <l n="10" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">The Conquest were his tho he met'em disarm'd.</l>
     <l n="11" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">They could not  of a rational nature,</l>
     <l n="12" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">That wou'd not relent at so moving a feature.</l>
     <l n="13" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">disguis'd he'el be thought by his Beauty;</l>
     <l n="14" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">And spar'd from the sense of a</l>
     <l n="15" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">Yet when I reflect on the Wounded and Dying,</l>
     <l n="16" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">In spight of my Courage it sets me a sighing.</l>
     <l n="17" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">But the  no danger can stay him,</l>
     <l n="18" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">Tho' I us'd all my Charms and Arts to delay him.</l>
     <l n="19" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">Yet oh ye kind powers you are bound to protect him,</l>
     <l n="20" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">Since he'es gone the bright way that Glory directs him.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
